Allow dhcp6-ll-wait "no" to skip link-local check and start dhclient6 immediately

Add support for dhcp6-ll-wait="no" as a config knob to bypass the link-local
address wait loop and start dhclient6 unconditionally. This is consistent with
the existing dhcp-wait="no" convention.

When dhcp6-ll-wait is set to "no", ifupdown2 will start dhclient6 immediately
without polling for a link-local address first. The dhclient6 daemon handles
the case where no link-local address is present yet by retrying internally.

This is needed for ZTP in-band discovery, where interfaces-config runs before
orchagent has had time to bring all ports up. With dhcp6-ll-wait="no" in the
ZTP DHCP policy, dhclient6 is started for all in-band ports immediately rather
than only for ports that already have a link-local address at that moment.

Upstream PR: https://github.com/CumulusNetworks/ifupdown2/pull/349
